text: Pierre Bottineau Library (formerly Pierre Bottineau Community Library) is a public library in northeast Minneapolis, Minnesota. The current library building was made in 2003. == History == In 2000, it was the only rented library and the smallest library in Hennepin County Library. The library could only have 40 people in at the same time.
